en: Le Privé opened in November 1993 in an old quarry surrounded by scrubland. A distinctive feature that acts as a strong link with the rich heritage of the Vaucluse region: the stone extracted from the site was destined for major architectural works such as the Pont du Gard (1st century), the Popes' Palace, the Pont Saint Benezet ("Avignon Bridge"), the city walls (11th and 12th century). But the historical dimension is obviously not the only anchor of the Private in his region: the club has set the rhythm of the nights around Avignon since its opening more than fifty years ago! It has become a mecca for nightlife, a must for hardened night owls and occasional revellers in the Avignon region. The arguments for its success are numerous: its isolation from the precious surrounding dwellings, numerous indoor and outdoor spaces (dancefloor for 400 people, heated summer/winter patio, 4 bars, a snack bar) and a generous capacity of 1000 people. The workmanship of its rough rock, its stone pillars, its vaulted passages is undeniably the "plus" of this inimitable establishment. The popular dimension of the discotheque is not contradictory with the electro vocation that the Private has adopted in recent years thanks to its ideal location, between Nîmes, Arles, Montpellier and Aix. It is this characteristic of a demanding club but open to all that its new operator Grossomodo is developing in 2009, wishing to remain faithful to the soul of the place. A recognized organizer for twenty years, responsible for the artistic success of Studio 88 in Aix-en-Provence ("Best Club France" at the Burn FG DJ Award 2007) for two years, Grossomodo unveils its ambition and its projects for the Private of the 3rd millennium: a solid artistic contribution for event evenings, the implementation of a "Best Everything" charter (Best Place, Best Welcome, Best Service, Best DJ's) in order to optimize the services of the club and the layout of the outdoor spaces as an open-air club. In November 2010, Privé was awarded the prize for "the best creation" at the Trophées de la Nuit, a new line in the establishment's prize list.establishment located 5 minutes from Avignon.private parking supervised all night long,Outside space in "Les Carrières" with terrace and covered patio and seating, Inside space in the historic cave with seating and dancefloor in the rock.
fr: Le Privé a ouvert en novembre 1993 dans une ancienne carrière entourée de garrigue. Un trait distinctif qui agit comme un lien fort avec la richesse patrimoniale de la région vauclusienne : la pierre extraite du site était destinée aux grandes œuvres architecturales comme le Pont du Gard (1er siècle), le Palais des Papes, le Pont Saint Benezet (“pont d’Avignon”), les remparts de la ville (11 et 12ème siècle). Mais la dimension historique n’est évidemment pas le seul ancrage du Privé dans sa région : le club a rythmé les nuits des alentours d’Avignon depuis son ouverture il y a plus de cinquante ans ! Il est devenu un haut lieu de la nuit, un rendez-vous incontournable des noctambules endurcis et fêtards occasionnels de la région Avignonnaise. Les arguments de son succès sont nombreux : un isolement des habitations environnantes précieux, de nombreux espaces intérieurs et extérieurs (dancefloor de 400 personnes, patio été/hiver chauffé, 4 bars, un snack) et une jauge généreuse de 1000 personnes. La facture de sa roche brute, de ses piliers de pierre, de ses passages voûtés est indéniablement le “plus” de cet établissement inimitable. La dimension populaire de la discothèque n’est pas contradictoire avec la vocation électro que le Privé a adopté ces dernières années grâce à sa situation idéale, entre Nîmes, Arles, Montpellier et Aix. C’est cette caractéristique de club exigeant mais ouvert à tous que son nouvel exploitant Grossomodo développe en 2009, désirant rester fidèle à l’âme du lieu. Organisateur reconnu depuis vingt ans, responsable pendant deux ans des succès artistiques du Studio 88 à Aix-en-Provence (“Best Club France” aux Burn FG DJ Award 2007) Grossomodo dévoile son ambition et ses projets pour le Privé du 3ème millénaire : un solide apport artistique pour les soirées événementielles, la mise en place d’une charte “Best Everything” (Best Place, Best Accueil, Best Service, Best DJ’s) afin d’optimiser les prestations du club et l’aménagement des espaces extérieurs en club à ciel ouvert. En novembre 2010, Privé s’est vu remettre le prix de “la meilleure création” aux Trophées de la Nuit, une nouvelle ligne au Palmarès de l’établissement.Établissement situé à 5 min d'Avignon.Parking Privé surveillé toute la nuit,espace Outside dans "Les Carrières" avec terrasse et patio couvert et places assises,espace Inside dans la grotte historique avec places assises et dancefloor dans la roche.

 But the historical dimension is obviously not the only anchoring of the Privé in its region: the club has given rhythm to the nights around Avignon since its opening more than fifty years ago! The craftsmanship of its raw rock, its stone pillars, its vaulted passages is undeniably the "plus" of this inimitable establishment. Recognized organizer for twenty years, responsible for two years of artistic success of the Studio 88 in Aix-en-Provence ("Best Club France" at the Burn FG DJ Award 2007) Grossomodo unveils his ambition and his projects for the Privé of the 3rd millennium: a solid artistic contribution for the events evenings, the implementation of a charter "Best Everything" (Best Place, Best Reception, Best Service, Best DJ's) in order to optimize the services of the club and the development of the outside spaces in open air club. In November 2010, Privé was awarded the prize for "best creation" at the Trophées de la Nuit, a new line in the establishment's list of achievements.

The establishment is located 5 minutes from Avignon.
Private parking monitored all night,
outside space in "Les Carrières" with terrace and covered patio and seating,
inside space in the historical cave with seats and dancefloor in the rock.
